'\"macro stdmacro
.TH TRUE 1 
.SH NAME
true, false \- provide truth values
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B true
.PP
.B false
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I True\^
does nothing, successfully.
.I False\^
does nothing, unsuccessfully.
They are typically used in input to
.IR sh\^ (1).
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
while true
.br
do
.br
.I 	command
.br
done
.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1).
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.I True\^
has exit status zero,
.I false\^
nonzero.
